						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone near the Īśvara temple outside the village.</p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II A.D. 1143.</p>						

						<p>This inscription, which refers to the reign of <hi rend="italic">pratāpachakravarti</hi> Jagadēkamalla, is dated in the 5th year of his reign, Dundubhi, Vaisākha Sunday. The details are very irregular. It records the death of Siṁgōja, son of <hi rend="italic">kammāra</hi> Kētōja, in a raid on the village.</p>						

						</summary>
